[Wind Direction]

2
00:01:35,630 --> 00:01:37,910
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:38,789 --> 00:01:42,570
[Summer 1987]

4
00:02:05,390 --> 00:02:07,320
Your son was born in the Year of the Snake?

5
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,320
He was born in the Year of the Dragon.

6
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:10,389
In 1954.

7
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,910
I was born in 1954.

8
00:02:13,220 --> 00:02:14,570
He was born in 1976.

9
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:19,280
He's four years older than your daughter.

10
00:02:21,990 --> 00:02:23,720
I was born in the Year of the Dog.

11
00:02:24,470 --> 00:02:26,630
You're four years older than me as well.

12
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:27,310
I know.

13
00:02:28,710 --> 00:02:30,310
Auntie Man told me

14
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:34,310
you'll get promoted soon?

15
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:36,090
Yes.

16
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:38,800
I'm going to work on the sea next month.

17
00:02:39,070 --> 00:02:40,500
Your presence at home in a year

18
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,760
can be counted on the fingers of one hand.

19
00:02:43,550 --> 00:02:44,829
What we do

20
00:02:45,570 --> 00:02:48,829
is surely not as easy as you guys working in the labor union.

21
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,890
But we're better than

22
00:02:50,910 --> 00:02:52,190
ordinary workers.

23
00:02:52,829 --> 00:02:54,350
Basically in a month,

24
00:02:54,390 --> 00:02:56,910
we work on the sea

25
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:57,940
for 20 days

26
00:02:58,390 --> 00:02:59,590
and take ten days off.

27
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:02,990
What matters is the great benefits.

28
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:06,070
What about your child

29
00:03:06,990 --> 00:03:09,050
while you're out working for 20 days?

30
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:13,110
Yeah, that's a problem.

31
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:15,810
So...

32
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:24,430
Why...

33
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:29,510
Why did you get divorced?

34
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:33,630
We didn't get along.

35
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:37,140
What about you?

36
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:40,310
The same as you.

37
00:03:40,990 --> 00:03:42,120
We didn't get along.

38
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:54,310
I think you are nice.

39
00:03:57,110 --> 00:03:57,990
You're, too.

40
00:04:20,110 --> 00:04:21,430
Explain it to me.

41
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,030
What did your mom mean?

42
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:24,150
How many times have I explained it to you?

43
00:04:24,150 --> 00:04:25,750
My mom didn't mean that.

44
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,190
She's kind yet sharp-tongued.

45
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:28,070
Forget it. Forget it.

46
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:28,990
No!

47
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:29,750
You think killing someone with a sharp tongue

48
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:30,870
will not be seen as murder?

49
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:31,630
I'm your wife,

50
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:32,380
part of the Yang family.

51
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:33,870
Why can't she treat me as part of the Yang family?

52
00:04:33,870 --> 00:04:35,750
Everyone treats you as part of the Yang family!

53
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:36,630
How can a family

54
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:37,820
have two household registration booklets?

55
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:39,310
We don't have time to get it done!

56
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:40,750
We'll find time!

57
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:41,710
If I don't mention it,

58
00:04:41,710 --> 00:04:42,510
you'll never have time!

59
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:43,909
Can you stop making trouble for me?

60
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:44,630
I beg you!

61
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:46,070
No, I can't!

62
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,060
Explain it to me!

63
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:48,030
Explain what?

64
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:49,470
What's there to explain?

65
00:04:49,470 --> 00:04:50,750
Explain why we have two household registration booklets!

66
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:51,430
What do you mean two?

67
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:53,510
We've had two household registration booklets since the very beginning!

68
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,590
In your mom's heart...

69
00:04:54,590 --> 00:04:55,790
We're one.

70
00:04:55,950 --> 00:04:56,990
You have me.

71
00:04:57,470 --> 00:04:58,909
You still don't admit it!

72
00:04:58,950 --> 00:04:59,750
How can I admit it?

73
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:00,750
Admit what?

74
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,710
What were you doing earlier?

75
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:04,110
Can you stop making trouble for me?

76
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:05,030
I beg you.

77
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,940
[What kind of family]

78
00:05:09,470 --> 00:05:10,210
Min.

79
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:12,550
Min.

80
00:05:14,910 --> 00:05:16,190
I bought you a dress.

81
00:05:16,210 --> 00:05:17,790
Look how beautiful the color is.

82
00:05:17,790 --> 00:05:19,550
A little girl like you will look pretty in it.

83
00:05:19,550 --> 00:05:20,110
Come on.

84
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:21,610
Try it on and let me see.

85
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,510
I don't wear dresses.

86
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,350
I'm not a little girl.

87
00:05:25,350 --> 00:05:26,510
I'm 17, Mom.

88
00:05:26,950 --> 00:05:27,910
So what?

89
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:28,950
Even if you are 70,

90
00:05:28,950 --> 00:05:30,310
you're a woman as well.

91
00:05:30,670 --> 00:05:32,700
Who says a woman must wear a dress?

92
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:33,760
I won't wear it.

93
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:37,980
That's weird.

94
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:39,990
When you were little,

95
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,840
you liked wearing dresses.

96
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:42,909
Why have you changed

97
00:05:42,909 --> 00:05:43,750
as you grow up?

98
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:45,350
What else do you want to do?

99
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,420
I want to have my hair cut.

100
00:05:48,470 --> 00:05:50,500
Have it cut short just like you do.

101
00:05:50,630 --> 00:05:51,670
Nonsense!

102
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:54,070
Why should a girl have her hair cut short?

103
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:54,790
Why not?

104
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:56,300
Your hair is so short.

105
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,430
How can you compare yourself to me?

106
00:05:57,430 --> 00:05:58,500
-Why... -How old am I?

107
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,710
How old are you?

108
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,410
Don't make me angry.

109
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:05,970
Uncle Yang said

110
00:06:06,690 --> 00:06:07,950
you're quite willful.

111
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,670
Can't you bring honor to me?

112
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:14,550
Don't let them laugh at us.

113
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:17,510
Do they laugh at us

114
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:19,590
because I don't wear dresses

115
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:21,540
and I want to have my hair cut short?

116
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:22,710
His family look down on us

117
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:24,510
from the bottom of their hearts.

118
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:32,230
Close the door for me.

119
00:06:32,990 --> 00:06:33,700
Shouldn't you

120
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,060
come back yesterday?

121
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,110
Why didn't you come back?

122
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,730
New equipment came.

123
00:06:39,020 --> 00:06:40,220
I couldn't walk away.

124
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:41,740
Then why didn't you tell me?

125
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:42,790
I paged you,

126
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:44,010
but you didn't reply.

127
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:45,700
My pager is out of power.

128
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:51,430
Did you drink?

129
00:06:52,290 --> 00:06:53,820
Yes, a little.

130
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:56,460
Did you get new equipment

131
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,909
or go for a drink?

132
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:00,190
Who did you drink with?

133
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,270
What's her name?

134
00:07:03,620 --> 00:07:05,470
Do I need to report my work to you?

135
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,400
You won't tell me, right?

136
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,870
Fine, I'll go ask them one by one.

137
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:09,390
I don't believe I can't get what I want.

138
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:11,650
What do you mean by asking them one by one?

139
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:12,790
Listen.

140
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:14,680
Hu Yue, don't make trouble for me.

141
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:16,720
I will make trouble for you.

142
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:18,120
Don't think I don't know

143
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:18,790
what you have done.

144
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:19,900
What have I done?

145
00:07:19,930 --> 00:07:20,910
You know it clearly.

146
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:21,830
I don't.

147
00:07:21,870 --> 00:07:22,710
Who is Ge Juan?

148
00:07:22,710 --> 00:07:23,670
Did you go out

149
00:07:23,710 --> 00:07:24,470
with Ge Juan for a drink?

150
00:07:24,470 --> 00:07:26,040
Why are you mentioning Ge Juan?

151
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,820
We worked together more than ten years ago.

152
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:28,700
So what?

153
00:07:29,310 --> 00:07:30,280
You won't admit it, right?

154
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:31,400
-Fine. -Admit what?

155
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,909
I'll go to Ge Juan tomorrow.

156
00:07:32,909 --> 00:07:33,590
I'll ask her.

157
00:07:33,590 --> 00:07:34,720
Why will you ask her?

158
00:07:34,790 --> 00:07:35,980
Listen, Hu Yue.

159
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:37,670
Don't you feel ashamed?

160
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:38,690
But I do.

161
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:40,150
In fact, I don't.

162
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:41,250
But if you want to protect her,

163
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,270
I'll give my consent.

164
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,530
I'll go to your leader.

165
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,510
I'll ask your leader to help settle the argument.

166
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:45,370
Why will you...

167
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,360
Hu Yue!

168
00:07:47,730 --> 00:07:49,170
Are you out of your mind?

169
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:52,300
I am!

170
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:58,470
Are you? We can go crazy together.

171
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:09,430
Are you going to piss me off too?

172
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:14,080
Kid,

173
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:15,580
don't take it too hard!

174
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:17,940
Yeah, you're still young!

175
00:08:18,570 --> 00:08:20,670
It'll be too late when you regret doing it!

176
00:08:20,670 --> 00:08:22,350
Whose kid is this?

177
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:24,060
She's Yang's daughter.

178
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,810
No, she's not.

179
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,510
She's not a biological one.

180
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:28,370
She's not a biological one.

181
00:08:28,370 --> 00:08:30,490
Come down, girl. Come down!

182
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:31,920
Come down! Come down!

183
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:33,630
How dangerous it is!

184
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:35,070
Hu Qiumin!

185
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:36,000
Hu!

186
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:37,080
Hu Qiumin, what are you doing?

187
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:38,159
Don't come over!

188
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:43,100
Hu, what are you doing?

189
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:44,480
Can you swim?

190
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:45,870
Since you're going to jump into the river.

191
00:08:45,870 --> 00:08:47,060
Didn't we agree

192
00:08:47,090 --> 00:08:48,730
we'll die on the same day?

193
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,040
Come down!

194
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:51,460
Oh no. I didn't mean

195
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,350
to be sworn siblings

196
00:08:52,350 --> 00:08:53,470
with someone seeking death so urgently!

197
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:54,910
How will she lead a life in the future?

198
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:56,390
There will be no life!

199
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:58,520
She'll die if she jumps off the bridge!

200
00:08:58,890 --> 00:08:59,750
Don't stop her!

201
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,030
I don't believe she dares to jump off the bridge!

202
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:02,910
She knows how deep the river is!

203
00:09:02,930 --> 00:09:04,280
People get drowned in the river every year!

204
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:06,100
People like her will get drowned within two minutes!

205
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,500
It's said those who jumped into the river were all pretty girls.

206
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,780
You're not a pretty girl yet.

207
00:09:08,780 --> 00:09:09,220
You...

208
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:11,290
Why did you have your hair cut?

209
00:09:11,290 --> 00:09:12,270
Come down first! Come down!

210
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:13,590
Shut up!

211
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,630
Stop being sarcastic.

212
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:17,860
Come down now.

213
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,690
Your parents are getting along.

214
00:09:19,830 --> 00:09:21,430
You have a warm family atmosphere.

215
00:09:21,430 --> 00:09:23,600
Mine is different from yours.

216
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:26,010
Do you know

217
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,950
what kind of life I've been living?

218
00:09:27,950 --> 00:09:29,520
Tell us then!

219
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:30,430
All these years,

220
00:09:30,430 --> 00:09:32,850
you've told us it was all right when you were asked.

221
00:09:32,850 --> 00:09:33,800
If you feel wronged,

222
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,170
tell us then!

223
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,040
Right.

224
00:09:39,070 --> 00:09:41,750
It's too embarrassing to tell you.

225
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:45,680
When I was little,

226
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,980
my parents fought each other every day.

227
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,700
Since I can remember,

228
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,480
there had been no peace

229
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:52,760
at home.

230
00:09:53,710 --> 00:09:54,790
When I was six,

231
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:56,910
my parents finally got divorced.

232
00:09:56,910 --> 00:09:58,350
I thought

233
00:09:58,370 --> 00:10:00,400
these stupid days were finally over!

234
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,120
However,

235
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,800
my mom got married again.

236
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,500
She fights and argues every day

237
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,900
as she did in the past.

238
00:10:08,690 --> 00:10:10,810
Yang Songbai, Yang.

239
00:10:11,380 --> 00:10:13,530
He didn't come back home once in a month.

240
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,180
He acted like a leader when he got back,

241
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:16,190
shouting at us.

242
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:18,280
My mom asked me

243
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:18,990
to be polite to him!

244
00:10:18,990 --> 00:10:20,190
Why should I?

245
00:10:20,230 --> 00:10:22,090
I'm not his biological daughter!

246
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,840
I don't understand!

247
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:27,630
Why would two people who don't love each other

248
00:10:27,630 --> 00:10:28,950
be together?

249
00:10:28,970 --> 00:10:31,170
Why would they build a family together?

250
00:10:32,070 --> 00:10:34,000
Why was I born

251
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:35,190
in this world?

252
00:10:36,660 --> 00:10:37,440
Do you know

253
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,310
how envious I am?

254
00:10:39,860 --> 00:10:41,820
You have a good family.

255
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,720
But I don't.

256
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:47,560
I don't. I've had enough.

257
00:10:47,590 --> 00:10:49,000
I've had enough!

258
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:51,040
I wish I could jump from here!

259
00:10:51,070 --> 00:10:52,120
I wish I could be born into a family,

260
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,710
in which there are no fights in my next life!

261
00:10:53,710 --> 00:10:54,440
Don't! Don't! Don't!

262
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,350
Hu! Hu!

263
00:10:55,470 --> 00:10:56,270
Listen to me.

264
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:57,350
Come down first, all right?

265
00:10:57,350 --> 00:10:58,590
You hate them.

266
00:10:58,610 --> 00:11:00,800
I'll scold them for you.

267
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:02,150
If they don't listen,

268
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:02,990
I'll ask Li Si

269
00:11:02,990 --> 00:11:04,430
to beat them up, okay?

270
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:05,030
The three of us stand a chance

271
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,270
to fight against the two of them, right?

272
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:07,270
I can defeat

273
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:07,870
both of them!

274
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,210
Come down first! Let's talk!

275
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,030
I'll uphold justice for you! Come on!

276
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:11,810
Min!

277
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,440
-I'll... -Hu Qiumin!

278
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,880
Come down!

279
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:18,220
What are you doing?

280
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:19,410
Auntie.

281
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:21,870
Come down!

282
00:11:22,570 --> 00:11:23,650
Come down! Do you hear me?

283
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,560
It's dangerous for you to be there!

284
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:26,640
Come down!

285
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:28,680
I beg you!

286
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:29,570
-Come down! -Min!

287
00:11:29,570 --> 00:11:30,330
Min!

288
00:11:31,260 --> 00:11:32,190
What's going on?

289
00:11:32,990 --> 00:11:34,590
What's she doing?

290
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:36,420
Min.

291
00:11:36,450 --> 00:11:37,290
Stay there!

292
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:40,090
It's none of your business.

293
00:11:40,090 --> 00:11:42,070
Stop trying to control me!

294
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:53,710
Pull her back.

295
00:11:55,010 --> 00:11:56,100
Don't you feel ashamed

296
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:57,200
in public?

297
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:58,980
You feel ashamed of us, right?

298
00:11:59,210 --> 00:12:00,310
Yes, we

299
00:12:00,310 --> 00:12:02,440
humiliated the Yang family!

300
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:03,650
Your whole family

301
00:12:03,650 --> 00:12:05,090
look down on us!

302
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:07,070
The most embarrassing thing I've ever done in my life

303
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:09,750
is marry you! Yang Songbai!

304
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:19,320
Min.

305
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,040
I was wrong.

306
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,330
I apologize to you.

307
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:26,750
I shouldn't have hit you.

308
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:28,740
Can you come down?

309
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,230
I promise

310
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:34,330
I won't meddle in your life, okay?

311
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:43,940
Come down.

312
00:12:45,420 --> 00:12:47,470
What should I do to get you down there?

313
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:48,660
Do you want me to kneel?

314
00:12:48,660 --> 00:12:50,020
Okay, I'll kneel.

315
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:50,640
Auntie!

316
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,410
What are you doing?

317
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:53,790
Mom, get up. Mom.

318
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:57,450
Mom, what are you doing?

319
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:01,480
Tell me.

320
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,000
Have you had enough of your life?

321
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,640
Have you?

322
00:13:15,670 --> 00:13:17,200
I've had enough of mine.

323
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:19,070
Auntie!

324
00:13:26,310 --> 00:13:27,270
Mom!

325
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:29,710
Mom!

326
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:35,960
[Linqi Oilfield Staff Hospital]

327
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:36,030
Li Si, why were you so impulsive?

328
00:13:36,260 --> 00:13:37,430
I wasn't impulsive.

329
00:13:38,690 --> 00:13:40,070
I was just being brave.

330
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:40,870
You know what?

331
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:42,910
I didn't even let go of her hand in the river.

332
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,510
Given my current situation,

333
00:13:44,710 --> 00:13:45,760
shouldn't you give me

334
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:46,720
an award or something?

335
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,920
Okay, I'll ask Hu

336
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:49,140
to write you a certificate of merit

337
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,390
which says you're not capable enough,

338
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,720
but what you did is commendable.

339
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,280
Luckily, nothing serious happened to you.

340
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,270
I fell into the river.

341
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:55,270
Isn't it serious?

342
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:56,450
I don't care.

343
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,390
Tell the school

344
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:00,740
to cancel the serious demerit for me.

345
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:03,230
And contribute to the broadcast room of the factory's TV station

346
00:14:03,230 --> 00:14:04,430
to sing my praises.

347
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,640
At this critical moment,

348
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:08,350
my dad has gone to the front line overnight.

349
00:14:08,350 --> 00:14:09,110
He

350
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:10,310
missed my good deeds.

351
00:14:11,190 --> 00:14:11,790
By the way,

352
00:14:12,830 --> 00:14:13,690
where is my mom?

353
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:15,320
She doesn't care about me as well?

354
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,710
Your mom. She is taking care of

355
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:18,240
someone who is truly brave.

356
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:19,780
Who?

357
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,580
Mr. Gao.

358
00:14:21,670 --> 00:14:22,640
Without him,

359
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:23,130
you would have been one kilometer

360
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:24,330
away.

361
00:14:27,150 --> 00:14:28,280
Do you know

362
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:30,890
who else jumped off the bridge to save you two?

363
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:32,670
Who?

364
00:14:33,950 --> 00:14:35,450
Madam, I really don't need it.

365
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:36,340
I'm fine.

366
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,630
I don't need to be hospitalized.

367
00:14:37,630 --> 00:14:38,380
No, no, no.

368
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,430
You have to

369
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:40,270
do a comprehensive examination.

370
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:42,150
What if there's a sequela?

371
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:42,740
No need, really.

372
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:44,190
Just stay in the hospital.

373
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:46,680
[Registration Office]

374
00:14:44,190 --> 00:14:45,950
I'll pay for everything.

375
00:14:45,970 --> 00:14:46,900
No need, really.

376
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:47,780
I used to be a member

377
00:14:47,780 --> 00:14:49,190
of the swimming team in college.

378
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:50,190
If I hadn't become a teacher,

379
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:51,450
I would have been a swimmer.

380
00:14:51,450 --> 00:14:52,750
I know how to swim.

381
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:54,960
Your clothes are ruined.

382
00:14:54,990 --> 00:14:56,590
I should at least give you a silk banner to thank you for what you did.

383
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:58,100
I'll buy you some clothes later.

384
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:58,550
No need.

385
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,870
If it weren't for you,

386
00:14:59,950 --> 00:15:01,490
something bad would have happened.

387
00:15:01,490 --> 00:15:02,350
I'm not the only one

388
00:15:02,350 --> 00:15:03,190
who saved them.

389
00:15:03,190 --> 00:15:04,490
A student in my class also helped them.

390
00:15:04,490 --> 00:15:06,300
Right, the student.

391
00:15:06,330 --> 00:15:07,510
Seems that he sent them here

392
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:08,500
and left within seconds.

393
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:10,700
I haven't had an opportunity to thank him.

394
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:11,900
It's okay. It's okay.

395
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:14,600
Mr. Gao, do you have a girlfriend?

396
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,420
Do you have a girlfriend?

397
00:15:19,350 --> 00:15:20,140
Not yet.

398
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:22,600
That's great.

399
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:23,630
Well...

400
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:25,640
My cousin is 23 years old.

401
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:27,130
She's my third aunt's daughter.

402
00:15:27,130 --> 00:15:28,250
She's also single.

403
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:29,550
My third aunt called me

404
00:15:29,550 --> 00:15:31,030
two days ago,

405
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:33,180
asking me to arrange this for her.

406
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,440
Yan graduated from a nursing school.

407
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,240
She's working in the county hospital now.

408
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,080
You two.

409
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:38,970
One is a teacher,

410
00:15:38,970 --> 00:15:39,990
and the other is a nurse.

411
00:15:39,990 --> 00:15:41,530
You two would be a perfect match.

412
00:15:41,530 --> 00:15:42,480
Thank you, Madam.

413
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:44,330
There... There's no rush.

414
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,390
I... I'm leaving.

415
00:15:45,390 --> 00:15:45,860
No. No.

416
00:15:45,890 --> 00:15:47,320
It's not about the rush!

417
00:15:47,350 --> 00:15:48,470
-I have no intention of that. -Gao.

418
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:49,550
Which year were you born in?

419
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:51,260
I was born in 1970.

420
00:16:10,930 --> 00:16:12,660
I'm going to find Yang Songbai.

421
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:14,100
Sister.

422
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:16,770
It has nothing to do with Yang.

423
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,000
Why will you go to him?

424
00:16:21,490 --> 00:16:22,860
Min is childish and easily loses her temper.

425
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:24,710
I get it.

426
00:16:24,830 --> 00:16:26,830
But I wonder why you did such a thing.

427
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:28,660
If you are not wronged,

428
00:16:28,660 --> 00:16:29,390
how could you

429
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,660
jump off the bridge without hesitation?

430
00:16:32,620 --> 00:16:34,480
We understand you wanted to scare Min

431
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:36,620
and prevent her from jumping off the bridge.

432
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:37,620
But why did you

433
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:38,770
jump off the bridge?

434
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:46,100
I was pissed off by Min.

435
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,120
I acted on impulse

436
00:16:48,590 --> 00:16:49,990
without thinking twice.

437
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:52,340
It really has nothing to do with Yang.

438
00:16:52,660 --> 00:16:53,330
Really.

439
00:16:53,710 --> 00:16:55,020
Don't go to him.

440
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:57,150
Isn't that embarrassing enough?

441
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,600
You're such a loser.

442
00:16:59,710 --> 00:17:01,040
All right, I'm fine.

443
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,120
You should go home.

444
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:03,960
Go home.

445
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,750
Fine. We're leaving.

446
00:17:09,109 --> 00:17:09,670
Let's go.

447
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:11,290
Call us if anything happens.

448
00:17:11,420 --> 00:17:12,750
No matter how late it is.

449
00:17:13,069 --> 00:17:14,390
Fine. We're leaving.

450
00:17:14,609 --> 00:17:16,140
-Have a good rest. -Go home.

451
00:17:16,530 --> 00:17:17,470
I'm fine.

452
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:20,329
Go in and be with your mom.

453
00:17:24,020 --> 00:17:24,950
You're leaving?

454
00:17:27,099 --> 00:17:27,700
Forget it.

455
00:17:32,910 --> 00:17:33,910
Just wait and see!

456
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:57,960
Why are you crying?

457
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:01,430
I think I should be the one crying.

458
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:08,870
Enough. Enough. Stop crying.

459
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:11,450
Or you'll be laughed at by others.

460
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:18,480
All right, stop crying, okay?

461
00:18:20,990 --> 00:18:22,310
Look at you.

462
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:24,390
Min was messing around.

463
00:18:24,390 --> 00:18:26,230
But why did you follow suit?

464
00:18:27,210 --> 00:18:28,530
Min is immature.

465
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:29,920
You're an adult.

466
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:31,740
But you behaved impulsively

467
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:33,010
and irrationally.

468
00:18:33,220 --> 00:18:34,310
Yang Songbai!

469
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:36,780
Why do you say my mom behaved

470
00:18:36,780 --> 00:18:38,230
impulsively and irrationally?

471
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:38,840
I... I...

472
00:18:38,870 --> 00:18:39,990
In your eyes,

473
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:41,150
dignity is more important

474
00:18:41,150 --> 00:18:42,430
than my mom's life, right?

475
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:43,270
No.

476
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:44,030
Why don't you think about

477
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:45,210
why she didn't hesitate

478
00:18:45,210 --> 00:18:46,360
to jump off the bridge just now?

479
00:18:46,360 --> 00:18:48,310
How can you say that now given what happened?

480
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:49,920
Are you still a man?

481
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:53,020
Min.

482
00:18:53,270 --> 00:18:54,180
It's true!

483
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,190
He and his family

484
00:18:57,230 --> 00:18:58,570
look down on us!

485
00:18:58,770 --> 00:19:00,510
It's fine that you look down on me.

486
00:19:00,510 --> 00:19:02,120
I'm not your biological daughter anyway,

487
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:02,720
right?

488
00:19:03,530 --> 00:19:05,330
But why do you look down on my mom?

489
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,430
My mom serves you every day,

490
00:19:07,430 --> 00:19:09,090
as if she serves an elder man!

491
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,280
How could you

492
00:19:10,310 --> 00:19:11,380
shout at her for so many years?

493
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:13,360
You treat her like she's your subordinate!

494
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,370
Is my mom your wife

495
00:19:14,390 --> 00:19:15,430
or your maid?

496
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:16,260
Min.

497
00:19:17,470 --> 00:19:18,110
How could you

498
00:19:18,110 --> 00:19:19,090
talk to me like this?

499
00:19:19,090 --> 00:19:20,160
Why couldn't I?

500
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:22,350
Let me tell you.

501
00:19:22,940 --> 00:19:24,230
I've had enough of you

502
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:24,870
being so overbearing at home

503
00:19:24,870 --> 00:19:26,240
all these years!

504
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,710
You're not that capable.

505
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:28,370
But when you get home,

506
00:19:28,370 --> 00:19:29,850
all you do is pick holes!

507
00:19:30,030 --> 00:19:30,670
Since you are so capable,

508
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:31,750
go out and order others around.

509
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:33,880
You're not a man if you can only be unreasonable at home!

510
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,280
Min, stop it!

511
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:36,060
Mom!

512
00:19:36,630 --> 00:19:37,590
You've been tolerant of him for so many years.

513
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:38,870
It's enough!

514
00:19:39,530 --> 00:19:41,930
You're still afraid of me confronting him.

515
00:19:42,650 --> 00:19:43,960
I am confronting him today!

516
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:44,540
What can he do?

517
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,530
Hu Qiumin!

518
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:50,980
I've raised you for so many years.

519
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:53,260
I'm one of your elders,

520
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:54,100
right?

521
00:19:54,550 --> 00:19:55,510
You're disqualified from making comments

522
00:19:55,510 --> 00:19:57,090
on what's going on between adults!

523
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:59,120
I'm making comments on you!

524
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,530
Listen!

525
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:02,030
This is my mom!

526
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:03,670
If my mom is wronged,

527
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:06,130
I will show no politeness no matter who it is!

528
00:20:07,870 --> 00:20:08,780
Do you hear me?

529
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:17,000
Okay.

530
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:40,260
Mom.

531
00:20:41,020 --> 00:20:42,420
Do you think

532
00:20:43,550 --> 00:20:44,640
there's a family where there are no fights

533
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:46,870
in this world?

534
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:47,840
No.

535
00:20:49,230 --> 00:20:50,270
Only strangers

536
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,240
won't quarrel.

537
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:53,310
Then, in your view,

538
00:20:53,630 --> 00:20:56,590
is divorce a bad thing or a good thing?

539
00:20:57,230 --> 00:20:59,430
Is it something you should think about?

540
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,450
Why, Dad?

541
00:21:02,470 --> 00:21:03,970
Why can't I think about it?

542
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,850
Divorce

543
00:21:06,590 --> 00:21:07,840
is not a good thing,

544
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:10,090
but it's not a bad thing as well.

545
00:21:10,090 --> 00:21:12,150
It's just a choice made in one's life.

546
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:14,570
Will you two get divorced?

547
00:21:15,370 --> 00:21:17,370
You still expect me to get divorced?

548
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:20,390
-Look at her! -Well.

549
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:22,190
She's discussing it

550
00:21:22,190 --> 00:21:23,470
with us,

551
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:24,030
right?

552
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:25,340
Don't get so emotional.

553
00:21:25,340 --> 00:21:26,790
Let's have a discussion. Come on.

554
00:21:26,790 --> 00:21:28,190
What's there to discuss?

555
00:21:28,260 --> 00:21:29,150
These kids

556
00:21:29,150 --> 00:21:29,750
are too young

557
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,230
to discuss the matter of divorce.

558
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:31,450
No. No.

559
00:21:31,450 --> 00:21:32,570
Isn't it too early?

560
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,630
-Step aside. -Look. Look.

561
00:21:33,630 --> 00:21:34,430
Divorce

562
00:21:34,430 --> 00:21:35,710
is a matter of a family.

563
00:21:35,710 --> 00:21:36,350
They

564
00:21:36,350 --> 00:21:37,850
are part of our family.

565
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:39,380
So they also have the right

566
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:40,750
to say something, right?

567
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:41,670
And I think

568
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:42,910
they now

569
00:21:42,930 --> 00:21:44,050
want to

570
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:44,600
seriously discuss this matter.

571
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,230
It means they're experiencing personal growth.

572
00:21:46,230 --> 00:21:47,230
They've grown up.

573
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:47,950
Yes.

574
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,520
I think,

575
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:52,910
if getting a divorce

576
00:21:52,930 --> 00:21:53,880
had been a matter

577
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,550
between parents,

578
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:56,830
Hu Qiumin

579
00:21:56,830 --> 00:21:59,270
wouldn't have wanted to jump into the river today.

580
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:01,430
She lives in a blended family.

581
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:03,890
That's different.

